josh roseman sextet events at stanford josh roseman sextet facebook twitter email print add to calendar brooklyn based trombonist composer and all around musical mad scientist roseman celebrates his jamaican heritage in this tribute to the founding fathers of dub and ska including trombonist don drummond a founding member of ska legends the skatalites a onetime skatalite himself and a downbeat 1 rising star trombonist roseman folds forward leaning jazz and electronica into the jamaican mix for a sound as fresh and cohesive as it is seriously funky generously supported by fred and stephanie harman part of the koret jazz project when saturday november 12 2011 8 00 pm where campbell recital hall braun music center map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students tags performance music arts sponsor stanford lively arts contact 650 725 arts 2787 livelyarts stanford edu admission general admission $24 permalink http events stanford edu events 284 28469 more info last modified november 2 2011
